cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on solving optimization problems in machine learning, specifically deep bilevel optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of penalty functions, which is a common technique in numerical analysis and optimization, suggesting that it could be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper presents results for data denoising and few-shot learning, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), respectively. Finally, the paper deals with large-scale optimization problems involving deep neural networks, which could also place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
